A comment here could prevent other people from falling into the same trap. Something like:

```c++
// If called with a stop_height, set the stop_height here to trigger a rescan to that height.
// If called without a stop height, leave stop_height as null here so rescan continues to the tip (even if the tip advances during rescan).
```

